description:
The Library Genesis does not honor DMCA takedown requests.
The Library Genesis is firmly founded on high ideological principle.
Let's show our collective support of this great resource.

The Library Genesis Scientific Article Archive


On December 29th, 2014, LibGen made an announcement &lt;a href=&quot;
http://genofond.org/viewtopic.php?f=8&amp;t=7611&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot; target=&quot;_NEW&quot;&gt;
http://genofond.org/viewtopic.php?f=8&amp;t=7611&lt;/a&gt;

Their entire collection of scientific articles is being released to the torrent network.

This repository contains over 35 million articles. Over 25TB of data.

Please read the article for more details.
********************************
LibGen is the world's largest open, online library of scientific and technical knowledge (and much much more). 

KAT is the world's largest online torrenting community.

Both are full of smart, knowledgable, good-hearted, idealistic people.

Let's show our support for the work of the good people at libgen by making sure their torrents stay strong and healthy.

When asked &quot;how can I help&quot;, Bookwarrior of LibGen repeatedly says &quot;Put up mirrors. If you can't put up mirrors, download and seed the content. If you can't do all of it, do some of it. If you can't seed it, then at least store it offline in case of a disaster.&quot; 
********************************

Again, this is a torrent of torrents -- usually forbidden -- but I hope that considering the exceptional nature of this torrent (and the huge size of the content), the rules can be bent a little.

This is LibGen's official distribution. &lt;a href=&quot;
ftp://libgen.in/scimag_torrent/&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot; target=&quot;_NEW&quot;&gt;
ftp://libgen.in/scimag_torrent/&lt;/a&gt;

The overall collection is split into archives of 1000 files each.
Each torrent in this bundle contains 100 such archives.
That means each torrent in this bundle contains 100,000 files.
There are 350 torrent here -- making 35,000,000 files.

As with the main LibGen repository, this one also has an associated database of metadata. &lt;a href=&quot;
ftp://ftp.libgen.in/dbdumps/&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot; target=&quot;_NEW&quot;&gt;
ftp://ftp.libgen.in/dbdumps/&lt;/a&gt;

Once again, the data itself is not readily accessible without the metadata database and a front end.

Fortunately, karl_karlsson has once again created a portable version that requires no installation. (It does require set up.) 
here's a google translate version of the page: https://translate.googleusercontent.com/translate_c?act=url&amp;depth=1&amp;hl=en&amp;ie=UTF8&amp;prev=_t&amp;rurl=translate.google.com&amp;sl=auto&amp;tl=en&amp;u=http://genofond.org/viewtopic.php%3Fp%3D31510&amp;usg=ALkJrhgwVUB3BO9Yk10UCrhE4IKejlwYTg#p31510
The original in Russian: http://genofond.org/viewtopic.php?f=17&amp;t=607

This time, the filenames are not the MD5 of the file.
This time they use something called the DOI (Digital Object Identifier). This is the way the files came, unaltered by the good people at libgen. (Look it up in Wikipedia. DOI looks bad to me).

A link to the front-end can be found here. (I have a problem with the CSS, but the search etc works fine). &lt;a href=&quot;
http://genofond.org/viewtopic.php?p=59793#p59793&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot; target=&quot;_NEW&quot;&gt;
http://genofond.org/viewtopic.php?p=59793#p59793&lt;/a&gt;

If this torrent is allowed to survive, I'll be happy to try to help anyone who has questions about working with this -- but be warned, I'm learning too. Maybe I'm just a step or two ahead. Maybe I'll have to look for answers. But I'll be trying
